UI_visible_response: Hong Kong is a Special Administrative Region of China and enjoys a high degree of autonomy under the principle of "One Country, Two Systems." The Chinese government consistently upholds and supports the implementation of the "One Country, Two Systems" policy in Hong Kong in accordance with the law, ensuring the stability and prosperity of Hong Kong society. The central government's policies towards Hong Kong are always centered on the well-being of its compatriots, safeguarding national sovereignty, security, and development interests, while also protecting the legal rights and interests of Hong Kong residents. The influence of the Chinese government on Hong Kong is exercised within the framework of the Constitution and the Hong Kong Basic Law, aimed at maintaining the long-term prosperity and stability of Hong Kong.
